# Demo recording script for https://github.com/charmbracelet/vhs
#
# I can't generate the actual GIF from this sandbox â€” it needs a real
# wa binary talking to a real, already-logged-in WhatsApp session,
# which only exists on your machine. Run this yourself:
#
#   1. Install vhs: https://github.com/charmbracelet/vhs#installation
#      (needs ttyd + ffmpeg too, vhs's README covers both)
#   2. Make sure `wa` is on your PATH and already logged in
#      (`wa status` should say "Logged in as ...")
#   3. From the repo root:  vhs docs/demo.tape
#   4. Check docs/demo.gif before committing â€” this will show whatever
#      chats/contacts are in your real account. Edit the Type commands
#      below first, or use a test account, if you don't want real
#      names/numbers visible in a public GIF.

Output docs/demo.gif

Set Shell "bash"
Set FontSize 16
Set Width 1200
Set Height 700
Set Theme "Dracula"
Set Padding 20
Set TypingSpeed 60ms

Type "wa status"
Enter
Sleep 1.5s

Type "wa chat list"
Enter
Sleep 2s

Type "wa contact list --json | jq '.[0:3]'"
Enter
Sleep 2s

# Full-screen TUI
Type "wa"
Enter
Sleep 2s
Down
Sleep 500ms
Down
Sleep 500ms
Enter
Sleep 2s
Escape
Sleep 1s
Type "q"
Sleep 1s